# List possible commands
terraform state


# List resources

terraform state list


# Show details of a resource

terraform state show <resource_address>


# Remove a resource

terraform state rm <resource_address>


# Move a resource

terraform state mv <source> <destination>


# Pull state

terraform state pull


# Push state

terraform state push <file>


# Replace provider

terraform state replace-provider <old> <new>

NOTE:

# Not part of terraform state

Refreshing reality → terraform plan -refresh-only

Creating new state file → terraform init/apply

Changing infra → terraform apply